>
> **** If you try to convert an old R12 system to 134A, you need to change
the
> expansion valve, compressor (because 134A uses higher pressures and
> compressors are preset), install barrier hoses and add more condenser
> capacity.

Actually, not always. If you convert an r12 system to r134a, only fill 85%
of original capacity. The system will work fine this way.

